            <title>[OAK-2073] Prevent against integer overflow in compaction check</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2073</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently there is a check in the Compactor which decides if a node is included in the compaction map based on its size. This is prone to the large size issue seen earlier with external binaries reporting a huge size, and might cause an integer overflow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
