                            <comment id="14119787" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 11:55:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My proposal is to turn the count itself into a long and also shortcut the check by verifying if the property size is bigger than the threshold.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; size = ps.size(i);
  count += size;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (size &amp;gt;= threshold || count &amp;gt;= threshold) {
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;this should cover even the sensitive &apos;external binary&apos; case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
